<div class="annotation_body embedly embedly_pro" data-embedly-width="450" data-id="3493890" data-video_id="">
  <div class="body_text" itemprop="description">
    <p>Marley wrote the song while flying out of Haiti, deeply moved by its poverty and the lives of Haitians, according his then-girlfriend Esther Anderson. The song was frequently performed at Marley’s concerts, often as the last song. “Get Up, Stand Up” was also the last song Marley ever performed on stage, on September 23, 1980 at the Stanley Theater in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.</p>
  </div>

  

  

  <p class="video_processing_message">
    This video is processing – it'll appear automatically when it's done.
  </p>

